column1: Supplementary Table 1: Fusion genes identified in EOC tumor samples and passing filtering steps.

1Discordant represents the discordant reads mapping to the gene pair. Junction Spanning Reads (JSR) are reads which maps to the gene-fusion exon junction and the mate end maps to one of the genes in the gene-pair. Perfect JSR are reads with 0 mis-matches. Junction represents the unique exon junctions that were found in the JSR. Position Consistency indicates if the mapping location of the discordant reads is consistent with the location of the spanning reads.  E-value and alignment length are derived from blastn using the longest transcripts of the gene pair in a fusion. Full details of PRADA output are available at: http://bioinformatics.mdanderson.org/main/PRADA:Overview#Documentation.
